{
  "texts": [
    "Evaluation 6.1 RQ1: Overall EffectivenessWe first measure the overall effectiveness of AutoCodeRover and baselines with the number of resolved task instances in SWEbench.",
    "With the goal of understanding to what extent the current AI systems can automatically resolve real-life software issues, the only inputs we provided are the natural language issue description and a local code repository checked out at the erroneous version.",
    "We repeated the experiment of AutoCodeRover three times to avoid randomness and presented the results in pass@1 and pass@3 metrics [8], which are denoted as AutoCodeRover @1 and Au-toCodeRover @3 respectively.",
    "When reporting time and token/cost for AutoCodeRover @3, we report the time and cost required for running each task three times.",
    "Since Devin was evaluated on a random 25% subset of SWE-bench [24], we also report results of Au-toCodeRover on this subset (we refer to this as \"SWE-bench Devin subset\")."
  ]
}